pr_body:
This adds the relevant docs for #782 

I also included a few other minor changes to the docs that I noticed while I was working on this.

@willingc if you'd be willing to look at this that would be fantastic!

@scottpurdy, this is what I have so far. It will need some cleanup and debugging, but I am presently blocked on Windows and OSX VM stability in Bamboo CI.

I created the corresponding [build plan]( https://ci.numenta.com/chain/admin/config/defaultStages.action?buildKey=BS-NUPIC) that is presently tied to my private branch that's the source of this PR. Since we don't have a manylinux wheel of nupic.bindings on PyPi yet, the Linux test is pulling a specific linux wheel from Numenta's S3. We will need a nupic.bindings manylinux deployment to PyPi and a matching change of nupic.bindings version in nupic's requirements.txt.

Once all is happy, the repository in this plan can be changed to nupic, and it can replace the existing nupic build plan. The nupic deployment project might need to be reconfigured, too.
